# [Aloha Editor - ${version} - The HTML5 WYSIWYG Editor](http://aloha-editor.org/)

## Zipfile content:

* /README - This file
* /aloha - Contains the build version of aloha with all examples and plugins
* /CHANGELOG.md - The Aloha Editor Changelog
* /LICENSE.txt - License information
* /guides - Aloha Editor Guides
* /api (Still under development)

## Variations of aloha.js

### Bare Version

The bare version of aloha will not include require.js, jquery-1.7.2.js, aloha-jquery-noconflict.js.

* aloha-bare.js
* aloha-bare.min.js - Minified version
* aloha.js - alias for aloha-bare.min.js

### Full Version

The full version of aloha will include require.js, jquery-1.7.2.js, aloha-jquery-noconflict.js.

* aloha-full.js 
* aloha-full.min.js - Minified version

## CDN (Content Delivery Network) Locations

Cloudfront CDN:
* http://cdn.aloha-editor.org/aloha-${version}/lib/aloha.js
* http://cdn.aloha-editor.org/current/lib/aloha.js

JSDelivr CDN:
* http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/aloha-${version}/lib/aloha.js
* http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/alohaeditor/current/lib/aloha.js

## Maven

You can include Aloha Editor in your maven project using the following dependencies:

	<dependency>
		<groupId>org.alohaeditor</groupId>
		<artifactId>alohaeditor</artifactId>
		<version>${version}</version>
		<type>zip</type>
	</dependency>

	<!-- The CDN Version of aloha contains no examples and no documentation --> 
	<dependency>
		<groupId>org.alohaeditor</groupId>
		<artifactId>alohaeditor</artifactId>
		<version>${version}</version>
		<classifier>cdn</classifier>
		<type>zip</type>
	</dependency>

	<!-- A sourcecode snapshot of the released version -->
	<dependency>
		<groupId>org.alohaeditor</groupId>
		<artifactId>alohaeditor</artifactId>
		<version>${version}</version>
		<classifier>source</classifier>
		<type>zip</type>
	</dependency>

